featured_reviews.review_id: The mosque is a place to gather for prayers, to study the holy qurhaan and to celebrate festivals such as Ramadan , bakrith. The mosque is open from before sunrise (at Fajr) to two hours after sunset (after Isha). Thus it is open all day to accommodate worshipers attending the five daily prayers. We recommend visiting the mosque during the prayer time so you will be able to meet other Muslims and learn from observation. There is a madarasha for childrens and separetely there is madarasha for girls ! At festive occassions like ramzan , bakrith , they conduct a prayer for womens in separate hall.
